    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-08-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-08-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="297"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <head>297. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Greece</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d297fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 881.10/8–360. Secret; Limit Distribution.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Athens</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1960-08-03T16:00:00+02:00">August 3, 1960, 4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>296. Re Embassy telegram 293.<note n="1" xml:id="d297fn1">Telegram 293, August 3,
                        reported that <persName corresp="#p_KK1">Karamanlis</persName> was
                        apparently holding up <persName>Gazis’</persName> departure for New York and
                        that Briggs would attempt to prod the Greek Government into action. (<hi
                            rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Extracting debt settlement seems about as difficult as pulling out walrus
                        tusk with eyebrow tweezers—frozen walrus at that.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>However, Secretary General Palamas now assures me that Gazis will leave
                        for New York “by this week-end.”<note n="2" xml:id="d297fn2">In telegram 367
                            to Athens, August 17, the Department informed Briggs that Gazis and
                            Munro initialed a memorandum of understanding on the debt issue on
                            August 11. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., 881.10/6–2960)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName>Briggs</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
